cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI 

This paper deals with efficient methods for approximating SPSD matrices, which is a common problem in machine learning and numerical analysis. The paper proposes a new method that is faster than existing methods while maintaining high accuracy. This makes it likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also involves data structures and algorithms for matrix manipulation, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses information theory and signal processing concepts, which could make it relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Signal Processing).
